-- China Stocks Rise on Easing Europe Concerns, Policy Outlook; Chalco Gains
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-26T05:37:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-26/china-stocks-rise-on-easing-europe-concerns-policy-outlook-chalco-gains.html

          
          
             China’s stocks advanced as the
results of European banks’ stress tests eased concerns about the
region’s debt crisis and brokerages predicted further gains 
for equities on valuations and possible easing of policy.  
 The Shanghai Composite Index, which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, rose for a sixth day, gaining 6.28, or
0.2 percent, to 2,578.31 as of 1:28 p.m. Aluminum Corp. of China
Ltd., the listed unit of nation’s biggest maker of the
lightweight metal, jumped 7 percent to 10.22 yuan.  
          
          


  


        